</emphasis>
General habitus stout (
<figureCitation id="DFFDE4B6FFB6FF80A57CFC8AE2EC8FE7" box="[603,688,1727,1750]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[151,182,2057,2076]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,756,2017]" captionTargetId="figure-291@2.[151,1436,746,2021]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Dorsal habitus of Cuccodorodes species. A – C. koshiensis sp. nov., male; B – C. weiperti sp. nov., male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4504760" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4504760/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="328">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
), body reddish brown, pronotum slightly darker, mouthparts and tarsomeres slighter in color, BL 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A52CFCCAE2ED8E27" box="[523,689,1791,1814]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.19" metricValueMax="3.36" metricValueMin="3.02" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="3.19" valueMax="3.36" valueMin="3.02">3.02–3.36 mm</quantity>
. Head about as long as wide, HL 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A695FD2AE20C8E07" box="[434,592,1823,1846]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.7" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="5.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="0.57" valueMax="0.58" valueMin="0.56">0.56–0.58 mm</quantity>
, HW 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A5AAFD2AE0988E67" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" metricValueMax="5.8999999999999995" metricValueMin="5.699999999999999" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="0.58" valueMax="0.59" valueMin="0.57">0.57–0.59 mm</quantity>
; vertexal foveae located far below level of posterior margin of eyes, sulcus evenly convergent anteriorly, more or less V-shaped (
<figureCitation id="DFFDE4B6FFB6FF80A67EFD4AE1F28EA7" box="[345,430,1919,1942]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[151,182,1339,1358]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,189,1320]" captionTargetId="figure-361@3.[151,1436,188,1321]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Male head and pronotum (A, C, E), and sternites 2–3 (IV–V) (B, D, F) of Cuccodorodes darjeelingensis sp. nov. (A–B), C. koshiensis sp. nov. (C–D), and C. weiperti sp. nov. (E–F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4504762" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4504762/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="328">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
), median carina extending anteriorly from near head base to meet sulcus; eyes small, slightly protruding laterally, each eye composed of about 10 facets; AnL 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A610FDEAE1888EC7" box="[311,468,2015,2038]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.19" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.18" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="1.19" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="1.18">1.18–1.20 mm</quantity>
. Pronotum wider than long, PL 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A79BFDCAE1058127" box="[188,345,2047,2070]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="6.2" metricValueMin="5.8" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="0.6" valueMax="0.62" valueMin="0.58">0.58–0.62 mm</quantity>
, PW 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A6B6FDCAE2738127" box="[401,559,2047,2070]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8500000000000005" metricValueMax="6.8999999999999995" metricValueMin="6.800000000000001" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="0.685" valueMax="0.69" valueMin="0.68">0.68–0.69 mm</quantity>
; median longitudinal sulcus extending from small median antebasal fovea to near apex, discal longitudinal sulci slightly curved, lateral longitudinal sulci strongly sinuate, broadening at basal half and densely setose. Elytra much wider than long, EL 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A482F9EEE4198AC3" box="[933,1093,987,1010]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.7" metricValueMax="8.2" metricValueMin="7.199999999999999" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="0.77" valueMax="0.82" valueMin="0.72">0.72–0.82 mm</quantity>
, EW 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A3A1F9EEE5748AC3" box="[1158,1320,987,1010]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="9.3" metricValueMin="8.7" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="0.9" valueMax="0.93" valueMin="0.87">0.87–0.93 mm</quantity>
. Abdomen widest at tergite 1 (IV), AL 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A37AF9CEE4A68D23" box="[1117,1274,1019,1042]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.145" metricValueMax="1.16" metricValueMin="1.13" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="1.145" valueMax="1.16" valueMin="1.13">1.13–1.16 mm</quantity>
, AW 0.89–1.00 mm; sternite 1 (IV) with broad and moderately thickened arched median projection (
<figureCitation id="DFFDE4B6FFB6FF80A37FFE0EE4F18D63" box="[1112,1197,1083,1106]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[151,182,1339,1358]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,189,1320]" captionTargetId="figure-361@3.[151,1436,188,1321]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Male head and pronotum (A, C, E), and sternites 2–3 (IV–V) (B, D, F) of Cuccodorodes darjeelingensis sp. nov. (A–B), C. koshiensis sp. nov. (C–D), and C. weiperti sp. nov. (E–F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4504762" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4504762/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="328">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
), surface of projection with scaly microsculpture, area surrounded by projection broadly triangular; median area of sternite 3 (V) lacking microsculpture; sternite 7 (IX) with membranous basal half broadly expanded (
<figureCitation id="DFFDE4B6FFB6FF80A316FE8EE4D98DE3" box="[1073,1157,1211,1234]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[151,182,2030,2049]" captionTargetBox="[155,1436,199,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[151,1436,195,1893]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 6. Male sternite 7 (IX) (A, D, G), and aedeagus (B–C, E–F, H–I) of Cuccodorodes darjeelingensis sp. nov. (A–C), C. koshiensis sp. nov. (D–F), and C. weiperti sp. nov. (G–I). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, D, G; 0.2 mm in B–C, E–F, H–I." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4504768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4504768/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="328">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
). Length of aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="DFFDE4B6FFB6FF80A24AFE8EE3148DC3" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[151,182,2030,2049]" captionTargetBox="[155,1436,199,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[151,1436,195,1893]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 6. Male sternite 7 (IX) (A, D, G), and aedeagus (B–C, E–F, H–I) of Cuccodorodes darjeelingensis sp. nov. (A–C), C. koshiensis sp. nov. (D–F), and C. weiperti sp. nov. (G–I). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, D, G; 0.2 mm in B–C, E–F, H–I." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4504768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4504768/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="328">Figs 6</figureCitation>
E–F) 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A4A4FEEEE3BE8DC3" box="[899,994,1243,1266]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.4" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="0.64">0.64 mm</quantity>
, ventral lobe strongly elongate, protruding posteroventrally; two markedly elongate sclerites at apex of ventral lobe and left side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4779F833FFB6FF80A47DFF0FE3318F43" blockId="7.[828,1437,859,1746]" pageId="7" pageNumber="328">
<emphasis id="75B22421FFB6FF80A47DFF0FE3EF8C63" bold="true" box="[858,947,1338,1362]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="328">Female.</emphasis>
General habitus similar to male; with slightly shorter antennae; each eye composed of about 9–10 facets; mesotibia simple; none of available specimens has median projection on tergites 3–4 (VI–VII); sternite 2 (IV) unmodified; genital complex (
<figureCitation id="DFFDE4B6FFB6FF80A3AFFF8EE4808CE3" box="[1160,1244,1467,1490]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[151,182,1286,1305]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,204,1259]" captionTargetId="figure-330@5.[151,1436,197,1262]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 5. Morphology of Cuccodorodes gen. nov., based on C. koshiensis sp. nov.unless specified otherwise.A – prothorax, in dorso-lateral view; B – meso- and metaventrite; C – internal foveal structure of tergite 1 (IV) and sternite 2 (IV); D–E – female genital complex, in dorsal view (D – C. darjeelingensis sp. nov.; E – C. koshiensis sp. nov.). Abbreviations: blf – basolateral foveae; dls – discal longitudinal sulcus; laf – lateral antebasal foveae; lls – lateral longitudinal sulcus; lmcf – lateral mesocoxal foveae; lmsf – lateral mesoventral foveae; lmtf – lateral metaventral foveae; mbf – mediobasal foveae; mls – median longitudinal sulcus; mmsf – median mesoventral foveae; mp – median projection; p – pit. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4504766" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4504766/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="328">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
) with basolateral extensions roundly narrowing posteriorly. Measurements: BL 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A445FFCEE3A28F23" box="[866,1022,1531,1554]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.975" metricValueMax="3.02" metricValueMin="2.93" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="2.975" valueMax="3.02" valueMin="2.93">2.93–3.02 mm</quantity>
, AnL 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A31DFFCEE4C68F23" box="[1082,1178,1531,1554]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.13" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="1.13">1.13 mm</quantity>
, HL 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A3ECFFCEE53B8F23" box="[1227,1383,1531,1554]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.7" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="5.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="0.57" valueMax="0.58" valueMin="0.56">0.56–0.58 mm</quantity>
, HW 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A41BFC2EE3858F03" box="[828,985,1563,1586]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.7" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="5.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="0.57" valueMax="0.58" valueMin="0.56">0.56–0.58 mm</quantity>
, PL 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A320FC2EE4348F03" box="[1031,1128,1563,1586]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="0.58">0.58 mm</quantity>
, PW 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A387FC2EE55D8F03" box="[1184,1281,1563,1586]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="0.68">0.68 mm</quantity>
, EL 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A215FC2EE3348F63" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.25" metricValueMax="7.4" metricValueMin="7.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="0.725" valueMax="0.74" valueMin="0.71">0.71–0.74 mm</quantity>
, EW 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A4BAFC0EE46B8F63" box="[925,1079,1595,1618]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.05" metricValueMax="9.2" metricValueMin="8.9" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="0.905" valueMax="0.92" valueMin="0.89">0.89–0.92 mm</quantity>
, AL 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A342FC0EE4A28F63" box="[1125,1278,1595,1618]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.11" metricValueMax="1.12" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="1.11" valueMax="1.12" valueMin="1.1">1.10–1.12 mm</quantity>
, AW 
<quantity id="803E55D6FFB6FF80A214FC0EE3358F43" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.65" metricValueMax="9.7" metricValueMin="9.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" unit="mm" value="0.965" valueMax="0.97" valueMin="0.96">0.96–0.97 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0FDCABB8FFB6FF80A41BFC4EE48D8F83" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="4779F833FFB6FF80A41BFC4EE48D8F83" blockId="7.[828,1437,859,1746]" pageId="7" pageNumber="328">
<emphasis id="75B22421FFB6FF80A41BFC4EE3E08FA3" bold="true" box="[828,956,1659,1682]" pageId="7" pageNumber="328">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named after 
<collectingRegion id="850236D1FFB6FF80A23FFC4EE5048FA3" box="[1304,1368,1659,1682]" country="Nepal" name="Kosi" pageId="7" pageNumber="328">Koshi</collectingRegion>
Zone, where the 
<typeStatus id="987D4691FFB6FF80A48CFCAEE3858F83" box="[939,985,1691,1714]" pageId="7" pageNumber="328">type</typeStatus>
locality lies; adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0FDCABB8FFB6FF80A41BFC8EE5018FE3" box="[828,1373,1723,1746]" pageId="7" pageNumber="328" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="4779F833FFB6FF80A41BFC8EE5018FE3" blockId="7.[828,1437,859,1746]" box="[828,1373,1723,1746]" pageId="7" pageNumber="328">
